dct_description_sm: Relief shown by form lines and spot heights. Depth shown by bathymetric isolines and soundings. Some sheets show hachures and shading. Principal meridian is Athens. Bookseller's label pasted on verso in French or Greek: "Maison cartographique, vente de cartes topographiques de Grèce, C. Grigouras & cie., Athènes, Grèce" or "K. Grēgouras & Sia, topographikoi chartai tēs Hellados & Balkaniōn, Athēnai." "Κ. Γρηγουρας & Σια, τοπογραφικοί χάρτης της Ελλάδος & Βαλκανίων, Αθήναι." Maps were trimmed on sides, top, and bottom. Map title, scale, and legend label are glued on verso.
dct_publisher_sm: Viennē : Eschediasthē kai etypōthē en tō. Kaisarovasilikō. Strat. Geōgr. Institoutō. en Viennē, [1908-1927].
